  <chapter id="introduction">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    
    <sect1 id="intro">
      <title>What is
      &mini-c;?</title>
      
      <para>This GNOME applet adds a command line to the panel. It
      features command completion, command history, changeable macros
      and an optional built-in clock.</para>

      <para>Because of the changeable macros you can use &mini-c; for
      many different tasks. You can simply start a program (or a short
      macro) or view a web page or search for a man/info page
      etc.</para>

      <para>&mini-c; has a handler on the left side which allows you
      to detach the applet from the panel.  This feature is especially
      usefull for people who use vertical panels.</para>
    </sect1>

